# Lifecycle-driven AI Red Teaming with ai\&me

## ***ai\&me*** provides **end-to-end AI assurance**, going beyond runtime filtering. It combines **automated adversarial testing**, **behavioural QA**, **real-time firewalls**, and **post-production analysis**, all tailored to your AI’s actual business context.

## Introduction

Securing generative AI requires more than runtime filtering. *ai\&me* provides full-lifecycle assurance—helping organisations detect, test, and respond to AI risks using context-aware tooling and integration-ready workflows.

This document outlines how we support that goal and references some of our recent customer success stories. It covers the following capabilities:

*     Contextual adversarial testing grounded in your business use cases  
*     Behavioural QA to simulate real-world conversations  
*     Integration with cloud-native guardrails like AWS Bedrock  
*     Post-production analysis to surface emergent risks  
*     Flexible deployment (SaaS or private cloud) to meet compliance needs

## Securing the AI Lifecycle—End-to-End AI Assurance

Our product supports adversarial testing and AI assurance throughout the entire lifecycle using contextual and customised red teaming. This helps you surface and mitigate issues early before they reach production. 

Furthermore, we enable organisations to automate and re-use tests 1\)  throughout pipelines, 2\) as an AI firewall and 3\) the foundation for AI-native monitoring. 

We plan to leverage our research to provide actionable insights and alerts on our logs that conventional deterministic monitoring cannot offer.

![][image1]   

We’re already supporting organisations in production. One example is **Eurolife FFH**, a member of the Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited and leading company in the Greek insurance market, which used *ai\&me* to automate testing for **OSCAR**, its AI-powered digital assistant for online customers.

A key takeaway from this collaboration was the value of our **automated assessment report**—a simple, shareable PDF generated from each test run. While human-in-the-loop feedback is supported, not every stakeholder has time to log in and review individual cases. The report enabled the product team to share concise, actionable findings with legal and compliance teams, supporting focused discussions and helping cross-functional stakeholders align on risks, mitigations, and policy boundaries—early and efficiently.

### Pre-Production: Contextual AI Assurance & Adversarial Testing

Our product supports both automated behavioural and adversarial testing before production (security and QA automation) and this is the key to shifting security to the left: Using your business context and logic it generates tailor-made adversarial attacks (security testing). Similarly, it produces an on-the-fly conversation with your AI to simulate and evaluate real-life conversational flows (behavioural testing).

We offer an easy-to-use environment to define and execute adversarial tests (Experiments).

The entire process—from synthetic data generation to LLM interactions, output evaluation, and reporting—is automated and driven by your initial business case input. Templates for the most common use cases provide an accelerated path to getting testing off the ground.

We consider this aspect of our product a unique differentiator that goes beyond boilerplate or generic tests. Instead, the context of the AI application is the grounding scope of tests. Furthermore, we incorporate expert human feedback to refine and improve the evaluation over time.

### Continuous Assurance with Pipeline automation

We provide APIs and Git-based workflows to integrate tests and experiments in CI and AI pipelines. This helps roll-out continuous assessment tailored to fit in the development and deployment workflows of your organisation.   

### Securing Production Deployments

We offer out-of-the-box **AI Firewall capabilities** that protect deployments by leveraging the results of contextual adversarial testing. This firewall acts as an additional security layer, enforcing business-specific boundaries and policies during live interactions.

Post-deployment, we provide **retrospective evaluation of LLM outputs** using LLM-as-a-judge and log analysis. This helps surface emergent risks or unsafe behaviours that may not be caught through standard runtime filtering. These insights support continuous improvement of your AI system’s safety and reliability in real-world usage.

## Complementing Cloud Provider AI Security Tools

Cloud providers like **AWS (Bedrock Guardrails)**, **Azure (AI Content Safety)**, and **Google Cloud (Vertex AI Safety Filters)** offer baseline runtime protections for generative AI—typically focused on content moderation, toxicity filtering, and prompt/output constraints. *ai\&me* complements built-in cloud safety tools by providing additional layers of context-aware security across the entire AI lifecycle. 

**Before deployment**, it runs contextual adversarial testing and behavioural QA tailored to your specific use case, helping to validate whether existing platform safety filters adequately address your business risks. 

**During deployment**, *ai\&me* acts as a context-aware AI firewall, sitting on top of platform-native guardrails to provide last-mile protection and enforce business-specific boundaries. 

**After deployment**, it performs retrospective analysis of logs and LLM outputs using an LLM-as-a-judge, supported by human-in-the-loop feedback. This process helps uncover issues that standard filtering may miss and continuously informs improvements to your AI safety strategy.

This lifecycle-based approach allows organizations to **augment native cloud protections** with deeper, more tailored security testing and observability.

## Compliance and Enterprise-Grade Security

The *ai\&me* platform is designed for secure, compliant use. We align with security best practices  to support enterprise assurance requirements, including:

* Data is encrypted at rest and in transit using industry standards.

* We enforce strong authentication (including SSO) and implement role-based access control (RBAC) to support multi-tenancy and enforce least privilege across users and environments.

* All activity—including test runs, feedback loops, and model interactions—is logged securely and with data protection. This provides secure and auditable logs, helping teams demonstrate due diligence and support governance workflows.

### GDPR & Data Residency

Our platform is fully GDPR-compliant and supports data minimisation, purpose limitation, and user access rights as standard. For European customers, all data can be hosted within EU-based cloud regions to meet local residency requirements. For organisations with stricter data controls, *ai\&me* can also be deployed as a private instance within your own AWS environment, ensuring full control and further enhancing compliance posture.
